WEBVTT

00:00.634 --> 00:03.352
Dre: <i>There are many different
ways to protect your family.</i>

00:03.353 --> 00:06.071
Now, I hate to be the paranoid
mom with the list of things

00:06.073 --> 00:07.473
that will kill her son, but...

00:07.475 --> 00:08.774
Mm.

00:08.776 --> 00:11.010
In-vitro was not cheap.
[ Chuckles ]

00:11.012 --> 00:13.679
<i>It's just that some ways are
way more annoying than others.</i>

00:13.681 --> 00:15.447
Okay, peanuts.
He can't have peanuts.

00:15.449 --> 00:16.382
Okay.
Gluten.

00:16.384 --> 00:17.433
Of course.
Black mold.

00:17.434 --> 00:18.483
Mm-hmm. Okay.
Why<i> black</i> mold?

00:18.486 --> 00:20.085
Hbo. What? What?

00:20.087 --> 00:23.055
That show "girls" makes him
want to talk to me

00:23.057 --> 00:26.358
about that show "girls,"
which makes me want to kill him.

00:26.360 --> 00:27.393
So I had to [Laughing]
put it on the list.

00:27.395 --> 00:28.928
Okay.

00:28.929 --> 00:30.462
So, uh, what...
Like, what, um...

00:30.464 --> 00:32.598
What time are you gonna
pick Seth up tomorrow?

00:32.600 --> 00:33.766
Oh, not till Sunday.

00:33.768 --> 00:35.151
Oh!
Oh, so, like...

00:35.152 --> 00:36.535
Oh, three whole days.
[ Laughs ]

00:36.537 --> 00:39.204
You can just forward his mail.

00:39.206 --> 00:40.706
I'm kidding.
I'm kidding.

00:40.708 --> 00:42.408
We are so happy
to be raising your son.

00:42.410 --> 00:44.343
That's nice. I see you
have smoke detectors.

00:44.345 --> 00:45.544
Mm-hmm. Yes. Good.

00:45.545 --> 00:46.744
I assume you have
a carbon-monoxide monitor.

00:46.747 --> 00:47.696
Mm-hmm.
Oh, yeah.

00:47.697 --> 00:48.646
Obviously you don't have a gun.

00:48.649 --> 00:50.315
No.
Yes.

00:50.317 --> 00:52.000
No, we don't.
We absolutely have a gun.

00:52.001 --> 00:53.684
You know, there've been a few
break-ins in the neighborhood,

00:53.687 --> 00:56.255
so I decided to get a gun
to protect my sneakers.

00:56.257 --> 00:57.823
Oh, and you guys.

00:57.825 --> 00:58.724
Right.
Mm-hmm.

00:58.726 --> 01:00.292
Yeah.
Oh, that...

01:00.294 --> 01:01.827
That makes [Clears throat]
makes perfect sense.

01:01.829 --> 01:04.496
Mm-hmm.
Seth, don't settle in!

01:04.498 --> 01:06.098
Seth!

01:06.099 --> 01:07.699
Why would you lie to her
about us having a gun?

01:07.701 --> 01:09.168
I don't know that woman.

01:09.169 --> 01:10.636
She might have been
a part of the break-ins.

01:10.638 --> 01:13.439
White people stole our freedom,
bow.

01:13.441 --> 01:15.774
You don't think they'll
come in here and steal my Xbox?

01:15.776 --> 01:17.376
Dre, this is serious.

01:17.378 --> 01:20.479
Yes, protecting my family
is very serious.

01:20.481 --> 01:23.082
That's why I've been talking about
getting a gun for years. Mnh-mnh.

01:23.084 --> 01:24.550
Even more now that
the kids are freaked out

01:24.552 --> 01:26.185
because of that break-in
on the next block.

01:26.187 --> 01:28.153
Bow, this bourgie neighborhood

01:28.155 --> 01:30.389
has lulled us into
a false sense of security.

01:30.391 --> 01:31.423
It's time to...

01:31.425 --> 01:32.391
Tool up.

01:32.393 --> 01:33.592
No.

01:33.594 --> 01:35.694
We are not getting a gun.

01:35.696 --> 01:37.162
Do you watch the news?

01:37.164 --> 01:38.697
Guns are very dangerous.

01:38.699 --> 01:40.165
Yeah, yeah.
You know what's dangerous, bow?

01:40.167 --> 01:40.766
What?

01:40.768 --> 01:42.534
Being murdered.

01:42.536 --> 01:44.503
By murderers.

01:44.505 --> 01:48.207
<i>But when it comes to the best
way to protect your family,</i>

01:48.209 --> 01:50.309
<i>there's still
a little bit of a debate.</i>

01:50.311 --> 01:52.344
<i>And it looked like me and bow</i>

01:52.346 --> 01:54.413
<i>were about to have
one big-ass debate.</i>

02:00.054 --> 02:01.887
Thank you so much
for everything.

02:01.889 --> 02:04.556
Something came up, and it has
nothing to do with the gun.

02:04.558 --> 02:05.891
[ Door closes ]

02:05.893 --> 02:07.292
Well, Seth is gone.

02:07.294 --> 02:09.895
Let's celebrate with
nuts and gluten.

02:09.897 --> 02:12.464
And even though I hate it,
let's watch that show "girls."

02:12.466 --> 02:14.433
This is not a joke.

02:14.435 --> 02:16.502
There's nothing funny about
the show "girls," bow.

02:16.504 --> 02:17.736
I'm not playing.

02:17.738 --> 02:19.471
We agreed on this.

02:19.473 --> 02:22.341
No,<i> you</i> agreed on this.
And I was right.

02:22.343 --> 02:24.643
Every day at work,
I see what guns do to people.

02:24.645 --> 02:25.577
Why do you want a gun?

02:25.579 --> 02:27.279
Why do I want a gun?

02:27.281 --> 02:28.847
For protection.

02:28.849 --> 02:30.182
Oh, and you don't feel
safe enough

02:30.184 --> 02:31.517
with all the ridiculous weapons

02:31.519 --> 02:32.684
you have stashed around
this house?

02:32.686 --> 02:34.653
They're not ridiculous.

02:34.655 --> 02:36.788
Under-counter
switchblade?

02:36.790 --> 02:39.258
Shower machete?

02:39.260 --> 02:42.694
Blender nunchuks?
Why?

02:42.696 --> 02:44.763
In case you get attacked
while making a milkshake?

02:44.765 --> 02:46.798
It's where
you're most vulnerable.

02:46.800 --> 02:49.234
Oh, my god.
Come on, bow.

02:49.236 --> 02:51.503
We'd all be a lot safer
if I got a gun.

02:51.505 --> 02:53.372
<i>Got</i> a gun?

02:53.374 --> 02:55.507
You mean we've been living
in this house without one?

02:55.509 --> 02:56.742
[ Sighs ]

02:56.744 --> 02:58.443
You've had us
flapping in the breeze?

02:58.445 --> 02:59.845
Okay, why don't you guys
go to your room?

02:59.847 --> 03:01.847
Why?
Is there a gun in there?

03:01.849 --> 03:02.915
Go!

03:02.917 --> 03:05.350
Unbelievable.
Mm-hmm.

03:05.352 --> 03:08.654
And there go two of the four
biggest reasons

03:08.656 --> 03:10.689
why we should not have a gun.

03:10.691 --> 03:13.959
They're two of the biggest
reasons<i> to</i> have a gun.

03:13.961 --> 03:16.195
Our children are frightened,
bow,

03:16.197 --> 03:18.597
and as their father,
it's my job to keep them safe.

03:18.599 --> 03:19.364
You're insane.

03:19.366 --> 03:20.766
Insane?

03:20.768 --> 03:22.834
We have a hard enough time
keeping Jack alive

03:25.706 --> 03:26.655
without a lethal weapon
in the house.

03:26.656 --> 03:27.605
Every day that boy doesn't drown
himself when brushing his teeth

03:27.608 --> 03:28.974
is a victory.

03:31.445 --> 03:32.678
No gun?

03:32.680 --> 03:34.346
I thought dad loved us.

03:34.348 --> 03:36.648
Apparently not,
or he would've strapped up.

03:36.650 --> 03:38.617
I'm such a fool!

03:38.619 --> 03:40.419
I've been sleeping with
my window open.

03:40.421 --> 03:41.920
Guys, relax.

03:41.922 --> 03:43.322
We don't need a gun.

03:43.324 --> 03:45.757
That kind of security
is fool's gold.

03:45.759 --> 03:49.928
The real threat to our family
and America is cyberterrorism.

03:49.930 --> 03:50.963
Here it goes.

03:50.965 --> 03:52.297
No one's watching the grid.

03:52.299 --> 03:53.966
What... the grid?

03:53.968 --> 03:56.301
Are you ever
on anyone else's page?

03:56.303 --> 03:57.769
God, I hope not.

03:57.771 --> 03:59.238
Wake up, sheep!
[ Gasps ]

03:59.240 --> 04:01.340
Cyberterrorism
has made burgling possible

04:01.342 --> 04:03.909
for fat guys who can't fit
through windows.

04:03.911 --> 04:06.745
So to protect us,
I'm gonna beef up our firewall.

04:06.747 --> 04:08.313
'Cause somebody has to.

04:08.315 --> 04:10.015
No, they don't.
Mm, no, they don't.

04:10.017 --> 04:11.483
It's your funeral.

04:11.485 --> 04:12.517
Bye, freak.

04:12.519 --> 04:15.137
[ Gasps ]
Hey,

04:15.138 --> 04:17.756
that girl Dominique Harris seems
like she's from a gun family.

04:17.758 --> 04:19.458
Maybe her parents will adopt us.

04:19.460 --> 04:22.578
Good idea.

04:22.579 --> 04:25.697
Should I go with adorable face
or sad-puppy face?

04:25.699 --> 04:27.399
I'll find it.

04:28.769 --> 04:30.636
Uh, excuse me?

04:30.638 --> 04:32.004
You know what?

04:32.006 --> 04:33.939
If no one wants to say it,
I will.

04:33.941 --> 04:36.341
I'm the real target.

04:36.343 --> 04:38.377
You guys are scraps!

04:38.379 --> 04:41.413
Well, if you really want to
learn how to defend yourself,

04:41.415 --> 04:44.950
I could teach you
the gentle art of karate.

04:44.952 --> 04:46.551
Thanks, pops, but I don't know

04:46.553 --> 04:47.686
if that's better than
having a gun.

04:47.688 --> 04:49.488
Yeah, I used to carry.

04:49.490 --> 04:51.323
And then someone took my piece
and used it against me.

04:51.325 --> 04:52.975
What happened?

04:52.976 --> 04:54.626
Your grandma Ruby shot me
right in the biscuit.

04:54.628 --> 04:58.664
But then I learned
the gentle art of karate.

04:58.666 --> 05:01.300
I became
a walking lethal weapon.

05:01.302 --> 05:02.834
See these guns?
They don't jam.

05:02.836 --> 05:05.704
No 10-day waiting period, and
I breeze right through tsa.

05:05.706 --> 05:07.039
Sounds ridiculous.

05:07.041 --> 05:08.740
All right, Zo-Zo.

05:08.742 --> 05:11.843
You are the one that said
you were the real target.

05:11.845 --> 05:13.979
Wa-wa-wait.
Come back.

05:13.981 --> 05:15.947
That's a solid point.

05:15.949 --> 05:17.983
I'm in.
And I need to learn today.

05:17.985 --> 05:19.318
Whoa.

05:19.320 --> 05:20.919
Martial arts is not learned
in a day.

05:20.921 --> 05:23.555
It's a long, lonely journey
that begins within,

05:23.557 --> 05:25.424
in which the student...
That's you...

05:25.426 --> 05:26.925
Never questions the master...
That's me.

05:26.927 --> 05:28.493
You understand?
Sure.

05:28.495 --> 05:31.997
So, are you ready to
begin your training?

05:35.969 --> 05:37.502
The lessons begin.

05:37.504 --> 05:39.771
Pledge on.

05:39.773 --> 05:42.007
Pledge off.

05:42.009 --> 05:43.642
Pledge on.

05:43.644 --> 05:46.378
What does this have to do with
learning karate?

05:46.380 --> 05:47.979
Everything.

05:47.981 --> 05:49.614
You missed a spot.

05:49.616 --> 05:51.383
[ Sighs ]
Pledge on.

05:51.385 --> 05:53.085
And we will get
maximum market penetration

05:53.087 --> 05:55.687
with a multi-platform
media blitz.

05:55.689 --> 05:57.556
Now, before I continue,

05:57.558 --> 06:01.393
does anybody want to interrupt
me with personal business?

06:01.395 --> 06:02.627
You know, I got something.

06:02.629 --> 06:04.563
- Yeah!
- Outstanding.

06:04.565 --> 06:06.398
I hate power point.

06:06.400 --> 06:09.101
I want to get a gun,
but bow is heavy against it.

06:09.103 --> 06:10.702
Get a gun, Dre.

06:10.704 --> 06:13.605
You gonna need one anyway
when it's time for the...

06:13.607 --> 06:15.407
Evolution-ray.

06:15.409 --> 06:17.442
You know, my girlfriend didn't
want me to have a gun.

06:17.444 --> 06:20.045
But I told her, "I'm a man.
Men have guns."

06:20.047 --> 06:21.580
Heh.

06:21.582 --> 06:25.117
N-now I'm on tinder, s-so...

06:25.119 --> 06:28.887
Well, I am a card-carrying
member of the nra.

06:28.889 --> 06:31.423
- Whoa.
- Geez, Stevens.

06:31.425 --> 06:33.725
I didn't know California
had an open carry permit.

06:33.727 --> 06:36.128
Well, I like to think of
the gun on my hip

06:36.130 --> 06:38.697
as the permit to
carry the gun on my hip.

06:38.699 --> 06:40.565
[ Chuckles ] Dre, just
be careful, all right?

06:40.567 --> 06:43.802
'Cause guns go off really easy.

06:43.804 --> 06:46.037
Like, really, really easy.

06:46.039 --> 06:48.106
Matter of fact,
get you a throwaway.

06:49.810 --> 06:51.410
Less questions.

06:51.412 --> 06:53.145
For who?

06:53.146 --> 06:54.879
Anyway, look, just let me know
when the gun shows up,

06:54.882 --> 06:57.549
because I have a great place for
us to go hunt the giant panda.

06:57.551 --> 06:58.984
Oh, yeah.

06:58.986 --> 07:01.686
Mr. Stevens,
those are endangered.

07:01.688 --> 07:03.855
Didn't say it was cheap.

07:03.857 --> 07:05.056
Here's how you convince
your wife, Dre.

07:05.058 --> 07:07.726
Y-you buy the gun,
and then you, uh...

07:07.728 --> 07:11.129
Well, you just point it
right in her face, you know?

07:11.131 --> 07:12.164
[ Chuckling ]
[ Stammers ]

07:12.166 --> 07:13.865
Unloaded, of course.
[ Laughs ]

07:13.867 --> 07:16.652
I'm not a crazy person, okay?

07:16.653 --> 07:19.438
<i>If I was seeing eye-to-eye
with the dum-dums from work,</i>

07:19.440 --> 07:21.506
<i>then maybe I was on
the wrong side of the issue.</i>

07:21.508 --> 07:23.575
<i>Maybe.</i>

07:23.577 --> 07:25.977
[ Sobbing ]

07:25.979 --> 07:27.813
What's going on?

07:27.815 --> 07:28.847
We were robbed.

07:28.849 --> 07:30.081
We were in the house,

07:30.083 --> 07:32.184
and they came in
through the back door.

07:32.186 --> 07:34.986
I was making a milkshake!

07:38.625 --> 07:40.025
It's where
you're most vulnerable.

07:40.027 --> 07:41.027
[ Sobs ]

07:44.865 --> 07:46.665
<i>Nothing makes a marriage
stronger</i>

07:46.667 --> 07:49.668
<i>than arguing over the most
polarizing issue in America.</i>

07:49.670 --> 07:53.572
I just don't think that
violence is ever the solution.

07:53.574 --> 07:56.741
Bow, the threat
is literally in our backyard.

07:56.743 --> 07:58.944
We're getting a gun.
So, you're saying to me,

07:58.946 --> 08:01.613
if Janine had a gun in her
house, she would have been safe?

08:01.615 --> 08:04.683
Yes! I'm saying people
protect themselves using guns.

08:04.685 --> 08:06.485
It's what they're for.

08:06.487 --> 08:09.187
Dre, statistics show that it
would've been used against her,

08:09.189 --> 08:11.590
or she would've shot herself
or her husband.

08:11.592 --> 08:13.058
Who still hasn't returned
our leaf blower.

08:13.060 --> 08:14.893
So, justice?
Oh, my god.

08:14.895 --> 08:16.928
Bow, it's not that I don't
understand your perspective.

08:16.930 --> 08:19.598
It's just that
your perspective is dumb.

08:19.600 --> 08:22.968
You are lucky we don't
have a gun in this house,

08:22.970 --> 08:24.269
'cause I would shoot you
right now.

08:24.271 --> 08:25.487
You wish you could.

08:25.488 --> 08:26.704
See, you're making my point
for me.

08:26.707 --> 08:28.006
Clearly there is no compromise.

08:28.008 --> 08:29.174
No, there isn't.

08:29.176 --> 08:30.509
That's why we're getting a gun.

08:30.511 --> 08:32.010
No!
Yes!

08:32.012 --> 08:33.545
[ Grunts ]

08:33.547 --> 08:34.813
Look at this.

08:34.815 --> 08:35.881
I've been keeping score.

08:35.883 --> 08:37.516
It's time for me to win.

08:37.518 --> 08:40.018
It's my turn!

08:40.020 --> 08:42.621
I did not have
your four children

08:42.623 --> 08:44.956
so you could die
and leave me to raise them.

08:44.958 --> 08:46.758
I'm not gonna...
Take it back!

08:46.760 --> 08:48.059
Can't never do nothing...

08:48.061 --> 08:49.678
[ Stomps ]

08:49.679 --> 08:51.296
That makes you look like
you ate Eddie Murphy.

08:51.298 --> 08:53.164
What?
Take it back!

08:53.166 --> 08:54.799
Never do nothing!

08:54.801 --> 08:57.135
You are not turning my sanctuary
into a gas-station bathroom.

08:57.137 --> 08:58.637
No, that...
Take it back!

08:58.639 --> 08:59.704
But you can pee standing...
Take it back!

08:59.706 --> 09:01.172
Never let me do nothing!

09:01.174 --> 09:05.010
I've been tanking arguments on
purpose just to win a big one,

09:05.012 --> 09:06.912
and getting a gun is a big one.

09:06.914 --> 09:08.847
Fine.
You want a big one?

09:08.849 --> 09:10.882
You can have a urinal.

09:10.884 --> 09:13.919
Too late.
The s.S.<i> Urinal</i> has sailed.

09:13.921 --> 09:15.153
We're getting a gun.

09:15.155 --> 09:16.254
Ba-bang! Ba-bang!

09:16.256 --> 09:17.822
Well, if you shoot
the way you pee,

09:17.824 --> 09:19.157
then we're all gonna be dead.

09:19.159 --> 09:21.026
[ Mockingly ]
Ba-bang! Ba-bang!

09:21.028 --> 09:21.993
Good night.

09:21.995 --> 09:23.061
Good night.

09:24.965 --> 09:27.732
Mmm.

09:27.734 --> 09:29.634
Mm.
Damn it.

09:34.107 --> 09:35.674
God.

09:35.676 --> 09:37.576
Look at him.

09:37.578 --> 09:39.311
That's<i> our</i> father.

09:39.313 --> 09:41.313
Let's go.

09:41.315 --> 09:43.315
[ Sighs ]

09:43.317 --> 09:44.983
Hey, hey, hey!

09:44.985 --> 09:46.618
Hey. Come here.
Where are you going?

09:46.620 --> 09:47.819
To Dominique Harris' house.

09:47.821 --> 09:49.354
We'll be safe there.

09:49.356 --> 09:51.222
What are you talking about?
You're safe here.

09:51.224 --> 09:52.691
Really?

09:52.693 --> 09:54.593
With<i> you</i> protecting us?

09:54.595 --> 09:56.728
Yes, really.
Uh-huh.

09:56.730 --> 09:58.330
This morning, we saw you

09:58.332 --> 10:00.332
trying to put your pants on
over your shoes.

10:00.334 --> 10:01.666
I did not.

10:01.668 --> 10:02.233
I have video.

10:02.235 --> 10:03.768
I...

10:05.172 --> 10:06.705
Thought they were boot cut.

10:06.707 --> 10:07.672
They weren't.
They weren't.

10:07.674 --> 10:08.807
But I get it.

10:08.809 --> 10:09.674
This is about the gun, isn't it?

10:09.676 --> 10:11.643
Don't worry.

10:11.645 --> 10:13.945
Don't worry.

10:13.947 --> 10:15.347
I'm all on this.

10:16.617 --> 10:18.183
I guess we should
give him a chance.

10:18.185 --> 10:21.186
We can't leave our safety
in the hands of that man.

10:21.188 --> 10:22.921
We got to start looking out
for ourselves.

10:22.923 --> 10:25.357
Well, I heard about
a documentary

10:25.359 --> 10:28.727
on security systems
for young kids.

10:28.729 --> 10:32.931
If this kid can protect
his family, so can we.

10:32.933 --> 10:34.866
<i>The twins were the final straw.</i>

10:34.868 --> 10:37.769
<i>So I went to exercise
my second-amendment right</i>

10:37.771 --> 10:38.937
<i>at a local gun store.</i>

10:38.939 --> 10:40.171
There's your shotgun, ma'am.

10:40.173 --> 10:44.909
Do... do you have class
for this to use?

10:44.911 --> 10:46.461
[ Scoffs ]
No, no, no.

10:46.462 --> 10:48.012
There's plenty of stuff
on YouTube.

10:48.015 --> 10:50.248
You...? Honestly, it's
mostly about confidence.

10:50.250 --> 10:51.349
Con...
Okay.

10:51.351 --> 10:52.183
Have fun.

10:52.185 --> 10:53.985
Oh, I don't know...

10:53.987 --> 10:56.321
Ehh, looks like you don't know.

10:56.323 --> 10:58.289
Hey, man, you're really gonna
sell her that?

10:58.291 --> 11:00.058
Why?
'Cause she's a woman?

11:00.060 --> 11:02.293
I'm about to sell one to you,
and you're a...

11:02.295 --> 11:04.229
Anyway, what
can I help you with today?

11:04.231 --> 11:06.398
I'd like a handgun, please.

11:06.400 --> 11:09.000
Preferably
one I can hold sideways.

